OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1782689571
OL,3,CCrucial rescue window narrows as
OL,4,CVenezuela enters third day after
OL,5,Cdeadly quakes
OL,7,FA website for people to register loved
OL,8,Fones believed to be missing has
OL,9,Freceived nearly 58,500 reports so far,
OL,10,Fwith no contact having been made with
OL,11,Fmore than 50,000 people.
OL,13,FAid agencies consider the first 48 to
OL,14,F72 hours to be a crucial time frame to
OL,15,Fretrieve people alive, though that can
OL,16,Fbe extended if they have access to
OL,17,Ffood and water.
OL,19,F"Each person saved is a miracle," said
OL,20,FJorge Rodriguez, president of the
OL,21,FNational Assembly.
OL,26,@|D@Krt
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
